      • start

        public void start()
        Calls all tests in this class one-by-one.

      • setUp

        public void setUp()
        Sets initial variables to a well-defined initial value. All test methods should be preceded by a call to this method

        Assigns a Guest object to the ot instance variable with the name "Ot" and assigns a Guest object to the sien instance variable with the name "Sien". Also assigns Room objects to instance variables k101 and k102 with numbers 101 and 102 respectively. Lastly, checks in sien in room k102.

      • testInitialcondition

        public void testInitialcondition()
        Test if the initial condition complies to the specification. This method should be preceded by a call to setUp().

      • testCheckinEmpty

        public void testCheckinEmpty()
        Tests checking in a new guest in an empty room. Calls ot.checkin(k101). This method should be preceded by a call to setUp().

      • testCheckinTaken

        public void testCheckinTaken()
        Checks checking in a new guest in a room that is already taken. Calls ot.checkin(k102). This method should be preceded by a call to setUp().

      • testCheckoutKnown

        public void testCheckoutKnown()
        Tests checking out a guest that rented a room. Calls sien.checkout(). This method should be preceded by a call to setUp().

      • testCheckoutUnknown

        public void testCheckoutUnknown()
        Tests checking out a guest that didn't rent a room. Calls ot.checkout(). This method should be preceded by a call to setUp().

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Makes a GuestTest object and runs it.
